  "text": "To distinguish between these two alternative hypotheses we have examined the association between (1) heterozygosity and hatching time in six strains of rainbow trout, and (2) specific alleles at individual loci and developmental time. The enzymes investigated in this study include glycolytic and citric acid cycle enzymes that are important energy yielding enzymes during early rainbow trout embryogenesis [CITATION_1] . A consistent association between genotypes at any locus and developmental rate in several strains would suggest that the enzyme products of this locus directly influence developmental rate.",
